# Enrolled approver PUBLIC keys (SSH allowed_signers format). This file is the TRUST ANCHOR for
# two gates and is CODEOWNERS-protected: an agent may edit it in a worktree but the real gates use
# the reviewed copy on main. Two signing namespaces are authenticated here:
#   algua-go-live      — the paper->live signed go-live ceremony (live_gate.py).
#   algua-human-actor  — an authenticated `--actor human` that unlocks gate relaxations (#329).
# A key enrolled only for one namespace does NOT authenticate the other.
#
# EVERY line MUST carry an explicit namespaces="..." restriction. An UNSCOPED line (no namespaces=)
# would be valid for EVERY namespace and collapse the separation above — verify_signature FAILS
# CLOSED if any enrolled line is unscoped. `registry enroll-approver --namespace <go-live|
# human-actor|both>` always writes a scoped line. One line per key:
#   <principal> namespaces="algua-go-live" ssh-ed25519 AAAA... comment
#   <principal> namespaces="algua-human-actor" ssh-ed25519 AAAA... comment
#   <principal> namespaces="algua-go-live,algua-human-actor" ssh-ed25519 AAAA... comment
